But, whatever be the number of true Gregorian variants in Class B, be the genuine instances comprised in it two, three or four, they are in the last degree unimportant. For we cannot say that in any ol them, as in A 1, Aa, A 3, A 5, A7, A9, is either of the competing forms more euphonious than the other; none of them, like A4, exhibits a manifestly good in contrast with a manifestly bad reading3 in none os them can we see marks ol a steadier grammatical purpose or apurer idiomatic standard; in none of them suppose that either ol the com· peting forms was suggested by the pressure of public calamity.

Let us now turn to Class D.
